LINE.Text: In July the Office of National Statistics revealed that the UK film
industry is the second largest contributor to UK economic growth
in the services sector, growing 8.9 percent in the last quarter alone -
and it seems that we have three big franchises to thank
Research: MARCUS WEBB Illustration: CHRISTIAN TATE Data: BRITISH FILM INSTITUTE (BFT)
The BFI operates a categorised points system to
determine a film's Britishness Those earning 18 points
or more out of a possible 35 are officially British
